puncture according to the procedures of the Clinical and Laboratory    Standards
 Institute (CLSI; formerly the National Committee for Clinical Laboratory    Sta
ndards or NCCLS) (19) and collected into a plain tube for serum vitamin B<SUB>12
</SUB>    and immunological analyses. Serum was separated immediately from the b
lood cells    and stored at –20°C until the tests were performed.</font></p>    
 ^cY#a05v22n6.htm##
