ace="Verdana">Qualitative detection of IgG antibodies to <I>Helicobacter    pylo
ri</I> was performed using a commercial enzyme-linked immunoassay (ELISA)    kit
 (Panbio, Brisbane, Queensland, Australia). This test was limited to a sub-sampl
e    of study participants (139 individuals), however, due to its high cost. A r
esult    was considered negative when the test indicated &lt;9 Panbio units, equ
ivocal    when between 9–11 Panbio units, and positive when &gt;11 Panbio units 
(21).</font></p>     ^cY#a05v22n6.htm##
